subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Write explanatory notes on two of the following: the development of an industrial estate; the localization of premises within a city; the decline of a particular industry; the importance of a river as a barrier; the position of a minor railway junction; the decline of a small port; the declining population of a parish; the cultivation of wheat; fluctuations in the height of the moorland edge.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Describe broadly the scenery of two of the following areas: South Downs; Peak District; Grampian Highlands; Southern Uplands of Scotland; the Fens.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: “British industries which depend on the New World tend naturally to be located in the west of the British Isles.” Discuss and illustrate.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Give an explanatory account of the density-distribution of population in the Great European Plain from the North Sea to the Urals. Illustrate by a sketch-map.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Give a brief account of the Alps and of their importance in the geography of Europe, mentioning their build, land utilization, and importance as a watershed and barrier.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Select two of the following pairs and show how they resemble or differ: Finland and Quebec; Belgium and Saxony; Portugal and North Island, New Zealand.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: What geographical factors contribute to the rapid growth of the U.S.S.R., and what factors impede its development?

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Show how the farming activities of the Indo-Gangetic Plain are related to climate. Illustrate by a sketch-map.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Discuss the similarities in situation between the capitals Ottawa, Washington, and Canberra, and between the largest towns Montreal, New York, and Sydney.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: What are the main colonial territories of France or Holland? Estimate their importance to the motherland.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Draw a map of the western coastland of South America showing the main climatic regions. Write descriptive notes on each region.

subject: GEOGRAPHY
text: Give a concise account of the geography of Japan or Palestine.
